description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a dynamic caring compassionate nurse who loves a challenge and wants to be part of a fantastic team?.....................Look no further for your next career step in leadership &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Complex Care Team aim is to empower and enable patients with complex needs to reach their full potential by providingcompassionate and caring family centred care. This unique service provides complex care packages for patients (adults and children) with continuing complex health care needs across Staffordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be responsible for day-to-day leadership and management of the team alongside our existing team leaders. Working together, the leadership team are responsive to the needs of their patients and families and provide high quality care packages. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will involve holistic assessment of patients and families, working closely with the commissioners and partners providing holistic care. The post-holder will be responsible for the direct line management of a number of B6 nurses and input into supervision and support for B2 and 3 Support Workers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work their hours flexibly to meet the needs of the service and be involved in strategic planning, quality assurance and raising the profile of the service. The service has standard processes that ensure consistency and evidenced based practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Midland Partnership NHS Foundation Trust is an excellent place to work. We are a forward thinking Trust with clear visions and values. We offer continual learning and development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 9th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on 23rd and 25th of November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Foran informal discussion please contact Julie Roberts Service Manager on 01283 352006 email julie.roberts2@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
